The chlorophyll a content (mg/L) was estimated according to Su et al. (2008). Two milliliter of culture broth was taken in a centrifuge tube and ultrasonicated for 10 min in an ice bath with 2 ml of 90 % methanol overnight. The homogenate was then centrifuged at 3,000 rpm for 5 min. The supernatant was separated and absorbance was read at 665 nm and the amount of chlorophyll was calculated using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
